text.section:
The provisions of subsection (3) of this section shall not apply to:
Pharmacist interns performing professional practice activities under the immediate supervision of a licensed pharmacist. The nature and scope of the activities referred to in this paragraph shall be determined by the board through administrative regulation promulgated pursuant to KRS Chapter 13A;
Pharmacist interns and pharmacy technicians performing specifically identified pharmacy practice activities while under the supervision of a pharmacist. The nature and scope of the activities referred to in this paragraph shall be determined by the board through administrative regulation promulgated pursuant to KRS Chapter 13A;
Other licensed health care professionals practicing within the statutory scope of their professional practices; or
Volunteer health practitioners providing services under KRS 39A.350 to 39A.366.
